	<text id="ruskin_to_joan_august_15_1867">
	
	    <header>
	        <inventNo>2003L01534</inventNo>
	    </header>
	
	    <body>
	        <div type="text">
	            <pb n="1"/>
	            <opener>
	                <placeName><!-- match letter exactly, delete if unnecessary -->
	                    <rs key="Q1025076" type="place">Keswick.</rs>
	                </placeName>
	                <date when="1867-08-20"><!-- match letter exactly, delete if unnecessary -->
	                    <rs type="date">Tuesday</rs>
	                </date>
	                <salute>My darling wee <rs key="76205504" type="person">Fernie</rs>,</salute><!-- match letter exactly, delete if
	                unnecessary
	                 -->
	            </opener>
	
	            <p id="p1">
	                <s id="s1">I fear you will be disappointed when you find this thick letter only a heap of various ones, but I
	                think most of them will interest you.</s>
	                <s id="s2">See message in <rs key="54018628" type="person">George</rs>'s about sausages and wine.</s>
	                <s id="s3">I have told <rs key="47523034" type="person">Miss Hill</rs> she may write to mama on the birthday Keep <rs key="c_hilliard" type="person">Constance's</rs> for me.</s>
	                <s id="s4">She complains much of you not writing to her.</s>
	                <s id="s5">I thought it was all the other way.</s>
	            </p>
	
	            <p id="p2">
	                <s id="s6">I am just leaving for <rs key="Q5599500" type="place">Langdale</rs> in a grievously wet day.</s>
	                <s id="s7"> I wrote to <rs key="95838041" type="person">Tom Richmond</rs> last night, giving up all thoughts of the
	                <rs key="Q390370" type="place">Windermere</rs> house - as far as I am concerned.</s><pb n="2"/>
	                <s id="s8">This climate is well enough for walking &amp; eating - but not for living in.</s>
	            </p>
	
	            <p id="p3">
	                <s id="s9">Did I tell you the saying of a little girl, communicated to me the other day by a
	                    clergyman's wife - "It's so difficult to know where God ends, and the Devil begins"</s>
	                <s id="s10">It is long since I heard something so comprehensive of all problems of human life - (and
	                weather! - How it does rain this morning!)</s>
	                <s id="s11">Nothing to answer I see - Thank mama for <rs key="lily_child" type="person">Lily's</rs> letter</s>
	            </p>
	
	            <closer>
	                <salute>Ever your loving Cuzzie</salute><!-- optional -
	                delete if
	                unnecessary -->
	                <signed><!-- optional - delete if unnecessary -->
	                    <rs key="73859585" type="person">JR</rs>
	                </signed>
	             </closer>
	
	            <postscript>
	            </postscript>
	
	        </div>
	    </body>
